<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE></DATELINE><TITLE>Coronavirus in Italy—Report From the Front Lines | Critical Care Medicine | JN Learning | AMA Ed Hub</TITLE><BODY>Physicians in Lombardy, Italy, have been overwhelmed by COVID-19 patients requiring critical care. Based on an existing ECMO center network they developed an ICU network to rapidly identify, triage, and manage patients infected with SARS-2-CoV. Maurizio Cecconi, MD, of Humanitas University in Milan discusses the region’s approach to the surge, including clinical and supply management, health care worker training and protection, and ventilation strategies, with JAMA Editor Howard Bauchner.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>